Question35
35 Write a PHP script using an array that checks if a string contains another string and displays the result.
ANSWER
<?php
// Main string to search within
$mainString = "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.";
// Array of words/phrases to search for
$searchTerms = array("fox", "dog", "cat", "quick", "elephant");
// Loop through the array and check if each term exists in the main string
foreach ($searchTerms as $term) {
    if (strpos($mainString, $term) !== false) {
        echo "The string contains '{$term}'.<br>";
    } else {
        echo "The string does NOT contain '{$term}'.<br>";
    }
}
?>

OUTPUT
The string contains 'fox'.
The string contains 'dog'.
The string does NOT contain 'cat'.
The string contains 'quick'.
The string does NOT contain 'elephant'.
